Definition: or תַּחְבּוּלָה; from {{h2254}} as denominative from {{h2256}}; (only in plural) properly, steerage (as a management of ropes), i.e. (figuratively) guidance or (by implication) a plan; good advice, (wise) counsels.
from an unused root meaning to depress; abasement; Tochu, an Israelite; Tohu.
a primitive root; to lop off; cut down.
or תַּזְנֻת; from {{h2181}}; harlotry, i.e. (figuratively) idolatry; fornication, whoredom.

or תֻּשִׁיָּה; from an unused root probably meaning to substantiate; support or (by implication) ability, i.e. (direct) help, (in purpose) an undertaking, (intellectual) understanding; enterprise, that which (thing as it) is, substance, (sound) wisdom, working.
from an unused root meaning to smite; a club; darts.
probably feminine of {{h8448}}; a custom; manner.

or תֹּשָׁב; (1 Kings 17:1), from {{h3427}}; a dweller but not outlandish [{{h5237}}]; especially (as distinguished from a native citizen [active participle of {{h3427}}] and a temporary inmate [{{h1616}}] or mere lodger [{{h3885}}]) resident alien; foreigner, inhabitant, sojourner, stranger.
(Aramaic) corresponding (by permutation) to {{h7794}}; a bull; bullock, ox.
or תֹּרָה; from {{h3384}}; a precept or statute, especially the Decalogue or Pentateuch; law.
or (feminine) תַּחֲנוּנָה; from {{h2603}}; earnest prayer; intreaty, supplication.
the same as {{h8467}}; Techinnah, an Israelite; Tehinnah.
or תַּחֲלֻא; from {{h2456}}; a malady; disease, × grievous, (that are) sick(-ness).
from {{h2490}} in the sense of opening; a commencement; relatively original (adverb, -ly); begin(-ning), first (time).
probably for {{h2453}}; sagacious; Tachkemoni, an Israelite; Tachmonite.
(Aramaic) or תּחֹת; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h8478}}; beneath; under.
from {{h2603}}; graciousness; causatively, entreaty; favour, grace, supplication.
from {{h2583}}; (only plural collectively) an encampment; camp.
probably from {{h2583}}; station; Tachan, the name of two Israelites; Tahan.
from {{h2554}}; a species of unclean bird (from its violence), perhaps an owl; night hawk.
or תּוּכִּי; probably of foreign derivation; some imported creature, probably a peacock; peacock.
patronymically from {{h8487}}; a Temanite or descendant of Teman; Temani, Temanite.
probably for {{h8489}}; Temeni, an Israelite; Temeni.
or תַּחְתֹּן; from {{h8478}}; bottommost; lower(-est), nether(-most).
the same as {{h8478}}; Tachath, the name of a place in the Desert, also of three Israelites; Tahath.
apparently from the plural masculine of {{h8482}} or {{h8478}} and {{h2320}}; lower (ones) monthly; Tachtim-Chodshi, a place in Palestine; Tahtim-hodshi.
from {{h8478}}; lowermost; as noun (feminine plural) the depths (figuratively, a pit, the womb); low (parts, -er, -er parts, -est), nether (part).
or תֵּמָא; probably of foreign derivation; Tema, a son of Ishmael, and the region settled by him; Tema.
or תִּיכֹן; from {{h8432}}; central; middle(-most), midst.
or תֵּמָן; the same as {{h8486}}; Teman, the name of two Edomites, and of the region and descendant of one of them; south, Teman.
or תֵּמָן; denominative from {{h3225}}; the south (as being on the right hand of a person facing the east); south (side, -ward, wind).
a facitious root from {{h2734}} through the idea of the heat of jealousy; to vie with a rival; close, contend.
for {{h8390}}; Tachrea, an Israelite; Tahrea.
probably of foreign derivation; a (clean) animal with fur, probably a species of antelope; badger.
the same as {{h8476}}; Tachash, a relative of Abraham; Thahash.
patronymically from {{h8465}}; a Tachanite (collectively) or descendants of Tachan; Tahanites.
or תְּחַפְנְחֵס; (Ezekiel 30:18), or תַּחְפְּנֵס; (Jeremiah 2:16), of Egyptian derivation; Tachpanches, Techaphneches or Tachpenes, a place in Egypt; Tahapanes, Tahpanhes, Tehaphnehes.
of Egyptian derivation; Tachpenes, an Egyptian woman; Tahpenes.
from {{h2734}} in the original sense of {{h2352}} or {{h2353}}; a linen corslet (as white or hollow); habergeon.

from the same as {{h8430}}; the bottom (as depressed); only adverbially, below (often with prepositional prefix underneath), in lieu of, etc.; as, beneath, × flat, in(-stead), (same) place (where...is), room, for...sake, stead of, under, × unto, × when...was mine, whereas, (where-) fore, with.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8478}}; under.
feminine passive participle of {{h8505}}; adjustment, i.e. structure; by implication, equipage; fashion, store.
from {{h3559}}; or probably identical with {{h8498}}; something arranged or fixed, i.e. a place; seat.
or תִּירֹשׁ; from {{h3423}} in the sense of expulsion; must or fresh grape-juice (as just squeezed out); by implication (rarely) fermented wine; (new, sweet) wine.
probably from {{h3372}}; fearful, Tirja, an Israelite; Tiria.
or תִּמָרָה; from the same as {{h8558}}; a column, i.e. cloud; pillar.
patrial or patronymically from an unused noun of uncertain meaning; a Titsite or descendant or inhabitant of an unknown Tits; Tizite.
or תּוֹך; (Psalm 72:14), from the same base as {{h8432}} (in the sense of cutting to pieces); oppression; deceit, fraud.
a primitive root; to strew, i.e. encamp; sit down.
probably of foreign derivation; Tiras, a son of Japheth; Tiras.
from an unused root meaning to butt; a buck or he-goat (as given to butting); he goat.
probably from {{h1129}}; properly, material, i.e. (specifically) refuse haum or stalks of grain (as chopped in threshing and used for fodder); chaff, straw, stubble.
from {{h1129}}; structure; by implication, a model, resemblance; figure, form, likeness, pattern, similitude.
from {{h8401}}; strawy; Tibni, an Israelite; Tibni.
from the same as {{h948}}; whiteness; Tebets, a place in Palestine; Thebez.
from {{h1197}}; burning; Taberah, a place in the Desert; Taberah.
or תִּגְלַת פְּלֶסֶר; or תִּלְגַּת פִּלְנְאֶסֶר or תִּלְגַּת פִּלְנֶסֶר; of foreign derivation; Tiglath-Pileser or Tilgath-pilneser, an Assyryrian king; Tiglath-pileser, Tilgath-pilneser.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7665}}; to be fragile (figuratively); broken.
from {{h1624}}; strife, i.e. infliction; blow.
from {{h1580}}; a bestowment; benefit.
or תַּמֹּר; (1 Kings 9:18), apparently from {{h8558}}; palm-city; Tadmor, a place near Palestine; Tadmor.
perhaps from {{h1763}}; fearfulness; Tidal, a Canaanite; Tidal.
apparently from {{h1725}}; enduring; a species of hard-wood or lasting tree (perhaps oak); pine (tree).
(Aramaic) from {{h1753}} in the original sense of enduring; permanence, i.e. (adverb) constantly; continually.
from {{h1984}}; laudation; specifically (concretely) a hymn; praise.
feminine of an unused noun (apparently from {{h1984}}) meaning bluster; braggadocio, i.e. (by implication) fatuity; folly.

from an unused root meaning to lie waste; a desolation (of surface), i.e. desert; figuratively, a worthless thing; adverbially, in vain; confusion, empty place, without form, nothing, (thing of) nought, vain, vanity, waste, wilderness.
or תְּהֹם; (usually feminine) from {{h1949}}; an abyss (as a surging mass of water), especially the deep (the main sea or the subterranean watersupply); deep (place), depth.
from {{h1980}}; a procession; × went.
from {{h2015}}; a perversity or fraud; (very) froward(-ness, thing), perverse thing.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8539}} or perhaps to {{h7582}} through the idea of sweeping to ruin (compare {{h8428}}); to amaze, i.e. (reflex. by implication) take alarm; be astonied.
a primitive root (or perhaps identical with {{h8427}} through a similar idea from scraping to pieces); to grieve; limit (by confusion with {{h8427}}).
a primitive root; to mark out, i.e. (primitive) scratch or (definite) imprint; scrabble, set (a mark).

from {{h3034}}; properly, an extension of the hand, i.e. (by implication) avowal, or (usually) adoration; specifically, a choir of worshippers; confession, (sacrifice of) praise, thanks(-giving, offering).
or תֹּגַרְמָה; probably of foreign derivation; Togarmah, a son of Gomer and his posterity; Togarmah.
from {{h3013}}; depression (of spirits); concretely a grief; heaviness, sorrow.
apparently from {{h2986}} (compare {{h2981}}) and {{h7014}}; offspring of Cain; Tubal-Kajin, an antidiluvian patriarch; Tubal-cain.
or תֻּבַל; probably of foreign derivation; Tubal, a postdiluvian patriarch and his posterity; Tubal.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7725}}, to come back; specifically (transitive and ellip.) to reply; answer, restore, return (an answer).
from {{h8427}}; a mark; by implication, a signature; desire, mark.
or תֹּר; probably the same as {{h8447}}; a ring-dove, often (figuratively) as a term of endearment; (turtle) dove.
probably the same as {{h8447}}; a manner (as a sort of turn); estate.
from the same as {{h3349}}; obedience; Tokahath, an Israelite; Tikvath (by correction for {{h8616}}).
or תֹּצָאָה; from {{h3318}}; (only in plural collective) exit, i.e. (geographical) boundary, or (figuratively) deliverance, (actively) source; border(-s), going(-s) forth (out), issues, outgoings.
or תֹּר; from {{h8446}}; a succession, i.e. a string or (abstractly) order; border, row, turn.
a primitive root; to meander (causatively, guide) about, especially for trade or reconnoitring; chap(-man), sent to descry, be excellent, merchant(-man), search (out), seek, (e-) spy (out).

or תֹּעֵבַה; feminine active participle of {{h8581}}; properly, something disgusting (morally), i.e. (as noun) an abhorrence; especially idolatry or (concretely) an idol; abominable (custom, thing), abomination.
patronymically from {{h8439}}; a Tolaïte (collectively) or descendants of Tola; Tolaites.
from {{h3286}}; (only in plural collective) weariness, i.e. (by implication) toil (treasure so obtained) or speed; plenty, strength.
feminine active participle of {{h8582}}; mistake, i.e. (morally) impiety, or (political) injury; error, hinder.

and (feminine) תּוֹלֵעָה; or תּוֹלַעַת; or תֹּלַעַת; from {{h3216}}; a maggot (as voracious); specifically (often with ellipsis of {{h8144}}) the crimson-grub, but used only (in this connection) of the color from it, and cloths dyed therewith; crimson, scarlet, worm.
the same as {{h8438}}; worm; Tola, the name of two Israelites; Tola.
from an unused root meaning to depress; humble; Toach, an Israelite; Toah.
from {{h3176}}; expectation; hope.

from an unused root meaning to sever; a bisection, i.e. (by implication) the centre; among(-st), × between, half, × (there-, where-), in(-to), middle, mid(-night), midst (among), × out (of), × through, × with(-in).

and תּוֹכַחַת; from {{h3198}}; chastisement; figuratively (by words) correction, refutation, proof (even in defence); argument, × chastened, correction, reasoning, rebuke, reproof, × be (often) reproved.
from {{h3205}}; posterity; Tolad, a place in Palestine; Tolad. Compare {{h513}}.
or תֹּלְדָה; from {{h3205}}; (plural only) descent, i.e. family; (figuratively) history; birth, generations.
from {{h8524}}; suspension; Tulon, an Israelite; Tilon (from the margin).
from {{h3213}}; causing to howl, i.e. an oppressor; that wasted.
